[Free living amebae are common in fresh water, where they rarely cause
conjunctivitis and meningitis. The infection is very difficult to treat but
very rare, illustrated by the small number of recorded cases. With a
hundred cases recorded during the past 30 years, the risk of infection in
the US is very low and clustering of three cases is unusual, but the data
on the cases diagnosed in Texas show a seasonal peak in July and August. -
Mod.EP
